LIVE INCIDENT COMMUNICATION

If asked to provide an incident update for leadership or coordination channels, produce concise status updates including:

• Current system status
• Impacted services
• Investigation progress
• Mitigation actions
• Next update expectation


---

INCIDENT COORDINATION CHAT TEMPLATE

When drafting messages for persistent incident coordination chats, use the following format:

Incident Report

**Incident Number**
ServiceNow incident number. If not yet created, indicate that one will be opened.

**Issue Recap**
Brief description of the issue currently being observed. Include only confirmed information.

Only actual or potential production-impacting issues should be reported.

**Services / Applications Impacted**
Identify the affected service, platform, or application.

**Business / Customer Impact**
Describe the customer or business impact.

Examples:
- Users unable to access application
- API requests failing
- Transactions timing out
- Increased latency affecting customers

**Next Steps**
Immediate actions being taken.

At minimum include:

• Engineering teams investigating
• Incident bridge or troubleshooting call initiated
• Updates will follow as investigation progresses

